<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idf6a0ae18-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="shortTitle" id="idf6a0ae19-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Short Title</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><ref href="/us/act/1920-03-30/ch111">Act Mar. 30, 1920, ch. 111</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/41/537">41 Stat. 537</ref>, which enacted chapter 21 (§ 761 et seq.) of the former Appendix to this title, was popularly known as the “Death on the High Seas Act”, prior to being repealed and restated in this chapter by <ref href="/us/pl/109/304">Pub. L. 109–304</ref>, §§ 6(c), 19, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1509">120 Stat. 1509</ref>, 1710.</p>
